  "notes": "2026-04-18: Implementation complete + code-reviewed, but E2E realtime delivery verification BLOCKED by Supabase Realtime tenant infrastructure failure for project [REDACTED_SUPABASE_PROJECT_REF]. Server-side realtime logs show persistent 'UnableToConnectToProject: Realtime was unable to connect to the project database' every 5-15s (even after the probe stops), with one prior 'Realtime.Tenants.Connect.CheckConnection executed in 494396 ms' (~8min) suggesting a stuck tenant cold-start path \u2014 this is beyond what the client can recover from. Work shipped this iteration: (1) migration us_044_applications_realtime_publication adds public.applications to supabase_realtime (default replica identity is sufficient because the client only reads payload.new.id+status); (2) app/(creator)/applications.tsx extended with a useEffect that calls supabase.realtime.setAuth(getCachedToken()) then subscribes to UPDATE events on applications filtered by creator_id=eq.<me>, patches rows in state on a status change, and fires the AC-specified success/error toast ('Your application was approved/rejected') for approved and rejected only (other 4 enum values patch the row silently since AC only names the two decisions); (3) a useRef mirror of `rows` (Codebase Pattern #82/#106) prevents stale-closure reads inside the subscription callback without forcing re-subscription on every list mutation; (4) mobile-mcp captured us-044-applied-pending-empty.png + us-044-applied-approved-empty.png proving the subscription wiring doesn't crash the screen under the DevRolePicker creator session (subscription is no-op there because the dev token is a literal string, not a signed JWT \u2014 same posture as US-036/US-043 per Codebase Pattern #122); (5) scripts/test/probe-us044-realtime.ts two-mode probe (signup | subscribe) that mints a real Marketify JWT via auth-signup-creator, calls supabase.realtime.setAuth(jwt), subscribes to UPDATE events under the same RLS policy (applications_creator_rw, polcmd='*') that guards the in-app stream, and asserts payload.new.status matches expected \u2014 ran end-to-end this iteration and returned FAIL with '[channel] status=TIMED_OUT' repeated four times because the broker never reached SUBSCRIBED. Probe test fixture (user_id a3495acd-7241-4d41-8e15-d42a210fdf65 + cascading rows) was cleaned up immediately via execute_sql. Code-reviewer returned 2 IMPORTANT findings, both carried over unchanged from US-036 (stale-token-at-subscription-time baseline across all realtime screens) and both AC-conformant (toast fires only on approved/rejected, matching the exact AC wording). Next iteration should re-run the probe (bun run scripts/test/probe-us044-realtime.ts signup then subscribe) once Supabase Realtime tenant is healthy \u2014 if verdict PASS, flip passes:true. Tenant hibernation/cold-start is the likely root cause; waiting for the tenant to warm up + checking get_logs({service:'realtime'}) for 'Starting stream replication for slot supabase_realtime_replication_slot_v2_83_2' (the postgres_changes slot, not just the messages slot) before running the probe is the recommended order. | 2026-04-18 06:43 re-verify: realtime tenant still broken \u2014 same TIMED_OUT pattern. New probe run signed up user 7ca930b8-...2297, seeded application 1d5d3800-...6350 against listing 11111111-...010, subscribed \u2192 4x TIMED_OUT then verdict FAIL. get_logs({service:realtime}) confirms only the broadcast slot supabase_realtime_messages_replication_slot_v2_83_2 ever starts; the postgres_changes slot supabase_realtime_replication_slot_v2_83_2 has not appeared in 24h. CheckConnection latency oscillates 476ms (healthy) \u2194 670s+ (cold-start) \u2194 tenant-shutdown-on-idle. No code change this iteration; fixtures cleaned up. Next iteration: re-run the probe as before; if get_logs shows the postgres_changes slot starting (search for slot name without the messages_ infix), the broker is finally healthy and the probe should reach SUBSCRIBED. | 2026-04-18 09:58 re-verify #3: tenant still broken. Per Codebase Pattern #124 decision rule, did NOT run the probe this iteration because get_logs({service:'realtime'}) STILL shows only the broadcast slot supabase_realtime_messages_replication_slot_v2_83_2 starting (never supabase_realtime_replication_slot_v2_83_2, the postgres_changes slot). Recent realtime log entries (last 24h window): 'Realtime.Tenants.Connect.CheckConnection executed in 672448 ms' + 'executed in 800322 ms' + 'executed in 672573 ms' (3 cold-starts each >11min), 'UnableToConnectToProject' flaring every 5-15s, tenant repeatedly hibernating ('Stop tenant [REDACTED_SUPABASE_PROJECT_REF] because of no connected users') \u2192 re-initializing \u2192 timing out again. The single 'executed in 476 ms' in the window was immediately followed by another hibernation cycle. Skipping probe execution saves a fresh probe-user fixture + cleanup cycle that would predictably TIMED_OUT; the get_logs observation is authoritative per the established pattern. Code unchanged. Next iteration: re-check get_logs first; only run the probe once you see 'Starting stream replication for slot supabase_realtime_replication_slot_v2_83_2' (WITHOUT the _messages_ infix) followed by absence of 'UnableToConnectToProject' for at least 60s. Supabase-side dashboard action (tenant restart / support ticket) may be required if the pattern persists into iteration #4+. | 2026-04-18 13:05 re-verify #4: tenant still broken. Followed the established decision rule (Codebase Pattern #124) and did NOT run the probe this iteration. get_logs({service:'realtime'}) over the last ~24h still shows only the broadcast slot supabase_realtime_messages_replication_slot_v2_83_2 starting (never the postgres_changes slot supabase_realtime_replication_slot_v2_83_2). Observed: 5 fresh 'UnableToConnectToProject' entries, CheckConnection latencies of 561ms (one healthy) vs 670537ms/672448ms/708088ms (three ~11min cold-starts), and repeated 'Stop tenant [REDACTED_SUPABASE_PROJECT_REF] because of no connected users' hibernations re-triggering the failed initialization cycle. No code change this iteration; work moves to US-056 which also requires realtime (same posture: ship implementation, defer end-to-end realtime verification to when tenant is healthy). Next iteration: re-check get_logs; only run probe-us044-realtime.ts once 'Starting stream replication for slot supabase_realtime_replication_slot_v2_83_2' (WITHOUT _messages_ infix) appears and 'UnableToConnectToProject' is absent for 60s+. Dashboard-side tenant restart / support ticket almost certainly needed by this point."
